body:
Maybe this would work? I think you can also drop the ref.current test because if ref.current is null, then select(null) will be empty and the code won’t do anything. (Maybe that’s too magical though…)

```suggestion
  useEffect(() => {
    const g = select(ref.current).append("g")
        .attr("transform", "translate(0, 4)")
        .call(axisBottom(x).ticks(5));
    return () => g.remove();
  }, [x]);
```
